** utbmciad-report **

LaTeX class and configuration file for typesetting a scientific or technical report following the template and guidelines from the "Connaissance et Intelligence Articielle Distribuees" (CIAD UR 7533) research laboratory <https://www.ciad-lab.fr>  of the "Universite de Technologie Belfort Montbeliard" in France.

Built on the powerful TeX-UPmethodology <https://www.arakhne.org/latex/tex-upmethodology> suite, it provides a professional, ready-to-use structure with advanced formatting macros.

This class and configuration file could be easily extended and adapted to the style for your own institution.

utbmciad-report is part of the larger project TeX-templates <https://www.arakhne.org/latex/tex-templates>.

1. Features

- Front page: Automatically generates the title page with:
  - Title, author, submission date, reference number
  - Institutional logos
- History of changes
- Complete lists: Table of contents, list of figures, list of tables, list of definitions
- Specialised environments: Definitions, theorems, research questions, objectives, contributions
- Advanced tables & figures: Full caption support and source references
- Inline enumerations: Compact lists within paragraphs
- Customised description lists: Flexible key‑value labelling
- Bibliographies: Two separate bibliographies (general and personal, e.g. own publications)

2. Requirements

- A recent TeX distribution (TeX Live 2020 or later, MiKTeX)
- The following classes and packages (automatically installed by most distributions):
  - TeX-UPmethodology <https://www.arakhne.org/latex/tex-upmethodology>, also available on CTAN as 'upmethodology'
  - Standard LaTeX packages (e.g. babel, graphicx, geometry, tocloft, etc.)

3. Download

The package is available for downloading from the official webpage <https://www.arakhne.org/latex/tex-templates/>.

4. Documentation & Tutorial

A complete tutorial with step‑by‑step examples is available at <https://www.arakhne.org/latex/tex-templates/report_tutorial.html>

